# Infrastructure (Terraform)

Infrastructure is modular Terraform under `infra/`. The root `infra/main.tf` wires four reusable modules in `infra/modules/`:

- `lambda` — one instance per function (`api`, `cron`, `worker`); zips `apps/<fn>/dist`, creates the function + IAM role.
- `api-gateway` — HTTP API (v2) `$default` route proxying to the `api` Lambda.
- `sqs` — main queue + DLQ, consume policy, and the event source mapping to the `worker` Lambda.
- `eventbridge` — schedule rule + target invoking the `cron` Lambda.

`infra/providers.tf` defines `local.resource_name` (`${project_name}-${env}`) and `local.common_tags`, applied as provider `default_tags` and passed to every module. Root outputs (`api_url`, `queue_url`, `cron_rule_arn`) live in `infra/outputs.tf`. Vars are in `infra/variables.tf` (`region`, `project_name`, `env`); state is remote S3 (`infra/backend.tf` + per-env `infra/backend/{dev,prod}.hcl`).

## Ops (justfile)

Run from repo root; the `justfile` sets `working-directory := 'infra'` and takes an `env` param (default `dev`):

- `just init <env>` — `terraform init` with the env's backend config.
- `just plan <env>` / `just apply <env>` / `just destroy <env>` — pass `-var="env=<env>"`.

## CD (`.github/workflows/deploy.yml`)

Pushes to `main` deploy `dev`; `workflow_dispatch` picks `dev`/`prod`. Auth is OIDC via `aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials` (`secrets.AWS_ROLE_ARN`, `vars.AWS_REGION`, `permissions: id-token: write`). It lints, builds, then `terraform init -backend-config=backend/<env>.hcl`, plan, apply.

## Add a Lambda function

1. Create `apps/<name>/` (build to `dist/`).
2. Add a `module "<name>"` block in `infra/main.tf` using `source = "./modules/lambda"`.
3. Wire any trigger (new `api-gateway`/`sqs`/`eventbridge` module call) and expose outputs in `infra/outputs.tf`.
